article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 77, Texas St. 72
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Mitch Rueter scored 20 points to lead Central Arkansas to a 77-72 Southland Conference victory over Texas State on Saturday. Rueter was 2-of-2 in three-pointers. Brooks Taylor scored 19 points and Marcus Pillow added 15. Brian Marks grabbed 10 rebounds. Central Arkansas (8-8, 1-2) was ahead by nine going into the half with 40-31 on the scoreboard. The Bears outshot the Bobcats in free throws for the second half, making 73.9 percent to Texas State's 63.6 percent. The Bobcats (8-8, 1-2) had four players in double digits. John Rybak scored 16 points; Ty Gough and Corey Jefferson each scored 12, and Brandon Bush added 11 points.
